text:
*Idea 1*
We know we already have shortage in different areas to treat patients, self assessment can greatly reduce the need for people to go for medical checkup and verification.
To address a larger mass, USSD can be utilized to do basic survey and guide people to take the right action.
For those that have access, a simple web form and/or apps can be created to provide the same service. We have something similar in the province I am in. <https://myhealth.alberta.ca/Journey/COVID-19/Pages/COVID-Self-Assessment.aspx>
Just need to have this verified against the advise the Ethiopian Health Ministry gives and localize it.
This might be a quick win in 3 different areas.
1 - Reduce panic and the congestion of the already limited health facilities in Ethiopia with unnecessary testing requests
2 - Can be used as part of the education process
3 - Identify people that need to be isolated and treated

I have shared the questions in the <#C010FHCRBPZ|bots-and-api> channel - <https://ethiopia-covid19.slack.com/archives/C010FHCRBPZ/p1584772226006300?thread_ts=1584770002.002800&cid=C010FHCRBPZ>

text:
Idea 3
I have mentioned this in the <#CVBQ5H16D|ui-ux> channel. We also need to focus on containing the spread from already infected individuals.

One way to see the isolation part is as protecting the more vulnerable individuals. So we need to showcase that the young and healthy can spread the virus and impact others more. Social Media ads will play a better role at dissonant this information. Some investment on Google ads, YouTube ads, FB ads might be necessary.

Supporting the already infected or self isolating people is another way to prevent spread. Trying as much as possible to eliminate the need for infected individuals from going out. Reaching out to services like Ride to deliver things like food/medicine purchase would be great.
